Class AbstractExpressionsSequenceStepSolver<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sri.ai.grinder.sgdpllt.theory.base.AbstractLinearStepSolver<T>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractSelectionStepSolver, MaximumExpressionStepSolver

    @Beta
public abstract class AbstractExpressionsSequenceStepSolver<T>
extends AbstractLinearStepSolver<T>
    An extension of AbstractLinearStepSolver that obtains the literals to be tested from a given list of expressions.

    More specifically, it implements makeLiteral() to pick the next expression e from a given list of expressions, and invokes a new method makeLiteralBasedOn(Expression) on e to obtain the next literal to be tested.

    Like other extensions of AbstractLinearStepSolver, implementations of this class must still define AbstractLinearStepSolver.makeSubStepSolverWhenLiteralIsTrue(), AbstractLinearStepSolver.makeSubStepSolverWhenLiteralIsFalse(), and AbstractLinearStepSolver.makeSolutionWhenAllElementsHaveBeenChecked().
